# Code Completeness Rules

These rules enforce completing all functionality before finishing any task. Incomplete code, pending TODOs, and dead code are prohibited.

## General Principle: Always Complete

**ALL described functionality MUST be fully implemented before finishing.**

It is not allowed to deliver partial code, with pending TODOs, or with errors indicating "not implemented".

## TDD as Completeness Requirement

**Code is NOT complete unless it follows the Test-Driven Development cycle.**

### Mandatory TDD Requirements for Completeness

Code completeness now explicitly includes:

- ✅ **Tests written BEFORE implementation** - Following the TDD cycle (REASON-RED-GREEN-REFACTOR-RE-EVALUATE)
- ✅ **All tests pass** - GREEN state achieved for all implemented functionality
- ✅ **Test cases list exists** - REASON phase completed with documented test cases
- ✅ **Tests follow Arrange-Act-Assert** - Tests are well-structured and maintainable
- ✅ **Tests are not skipped** - No `.skip()` or commented-out tests
- ✅ **Existing tests remain passing** - No regressions introduced

### Code Without Tests is Incomplete Code

**Delivering implementation without tests violates completeness rules.**

```typescript
// ❌ INCOMPLETE - Implementation without tests
@Injectable()
export class CreateTagUseCase {
  async execute(input: CreateTagDto): Promise<Tag> {
    // Full implementation here
    const tag = Tag.create({ name: input.name })
    return await this.repository.save(tag)
  }
}
// ❌ No test file exists - CODE IS INCOMPLETE

// ✅ COMPLETE - Implementation with tests
// File: create-tag.use-case.ts
@Injectable()
export class CreateTagUseCase {
  async execute(input: CreateTagDto): Promise<Tag> {
    const tag = Tag.create({ name: input.name })
    return await this.repository.save(tag)
  }
}

// File: __tests__/create-tag.use-case.test.ts
describe('CreateTagUseCase', () => {
  test('should create tag with valid name', async () => {
    // Test implementation following TDD cycle
  })
})
// ✅ Tests exist and pass - CODE IS COMPLETE
```

### TDD Integration with Completeness Verification

When verifying code completeness, also verify:

- ✅ Test file exists for every implementation file
- ✅ Test cases list was created (REASON phase)
- ✅ Tests were written before implementation (RED phase)
- ✅ All tests pass (GREEN phase achieved)
- ✅ Code was refactored with tests remaining green (REFACTOR phase)
- ✅ Test cases list shows completion status (RE-EVALUATE phase)

**Reference**: See `.cursor/rules/tdd-cycle.mdc` for mandatory TDD workflow details.

**Reference**: See `.cursor/rules/agent-tdd-enforcement.mdc` for agent-specific TDD requirements.

## Absolute Prohibitions

### ❌ FORBIDDEN: TODO/FIXME/XXX/HACK Comments

Never leave TODO, FIXME, XXX, or HACK comments in the code.

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT - Pending TODO
async execute(input: { id: string }): Promise<Tag> {
  // TODO: Add validation
  const tag = await this.repository.findById(input.id)
  return tag
}

// ❌ INCORRECT - Pending FIXME
function processData(data: Data): Result {
  // FIXME: Handle edge case
  return data.process()
}
```

### ❌ FORBIDDEN: "Not yet implemented" Errors

Never use `throw new Error('... not yet implemented')` or similar variants.

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT - "Not implemented" error
async execute(input: CreateTagDto): Promise<Tag> {
  // TODO: Implement backend endpoint
  throw new Error('Create tag endpoint not yet implemented in backend')
}

// ❌ INCORRECT - Unimplemented function
function complexCalculation(input: Input): Output {
  throw new Error('Function not yet implemented')
}
```

### ❌ FORBIDDEN: Empty or Partial Files

Never create or leave empty files, or files that only contain comments without implementation.

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT - Empty file or only comments
// This service will handle X functionality
// Implementation pending

// ❌ INCORRECT - File with only empty exports
export class Service {
  // Implementation pending
}
```

### ❌ FORBIDDEN: Partial Functionality

If a functionality is described, it must be fully implemented.

```typescript
// ❌ INCORRECT - Incomplete validation
async validateEmail(email: string): Promise<boolean> {
  // Should validate format and check uniqueness
  return email.includes('@') // Incomplete validation
}

// ❌ INCORRECT - Function with missing logic
async saveEvent(event: Event): Promise<Event> {
  const saved = await this.repository.save(event)
  // Missing: publish event, update cache, send notification
  return saved
}
```

## Correct Patterns

### ✅ CORRECT - Complete Implementation

All functionality must be fully implemented:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class CreateTagUseCase {
  constructor(
    @Inject(TagPrismaRepository)
    private readonly tagRepository: TagPrismaRepository,
    @Inject(EventBus)
    private readonly eventBus: EventBus,
    @Inject(Logger)
    private readonly logger: Logger,
  ) {}

  async execute(input: CreateTagDto): Promise<Tag> {
    // ✅ Complete validation
    const tagName = TagName.create(input.name)
    
    // ✅ Check for duplicates
    const existing = await this.tagRepository.findByName(tagName)
    if (existing) {
      throw new OneJsError(
        'Tag already exists',
        409,
        `Tag with name "${input.name}" already exists`,
        { name: input.name },
        ErrorCodes.RESOURCE_ALREADY_EXISTS
      )
    }

    // ✅ Create entity
    const tag = Tag.create({ name: tagName })

    // ✅ Persist
    const savedTag = await this.tagRepository.save(tag)

    // ✅ Publish event
    await this.eventBus.publish(new TagCreatedEvent(savedTag.toEventDto()))

    // ✅ Return result
    return savedTag
  }
}
```

### ✅ CORRECT - Complete Code Without TODOs

```typescript
async execute(input: { email: string }): Promise<User> {
  // ✅ Complete email validation
  if (!this.isValidEmail(input.email)) {
    throw new OneJsError(
      'Invalid email',
      400,
      `Email "${input.email}" is not valid`,
      { email: input.email },
      ErrorCodes.VALIDATION_ERROR
    )
  }

  // ✅ Complete duplicate check
  const existing = await this.repository.findByEmail(input.email)
  if (existing) {
    throw new OneJsError(
      'Email already exists',
      409,
      `User with email "${input.email}" already exists`,
      { email: input.email },
      ErrorCodes.RESOURCE_ALREADY_EXISTS
    )
  }

  // ✅ Complete creation
  const user = User.create({ email: input.email })
  return await this.repository.save(user)
}
```

## Dead Code Cleanup

### Remove Unused Code

Always remove:
- Functions/methods that are never called
- Unused variables/constants
- Unused imports
- Exports that are never imported
- Complete unused files

### ✅ CORRECT - Clean Code

```typescript
// ✅ Only imports that are used
import { TagRepository } from './tag.repository'
import { OneJsError } from '@OneJs/Core'

@Injectable()
export class GetTagUseCase {
  constructor(
    @Inject(TagRepository)
    private readonly tagRepository: TagRepository,
  ) {}

  // ✅ Function that is used and called
  async execute(input: { id: string }): Promise<Tag> {
    const tag = await this.tagRepository.findById(input.id)
    if (!tag) {
      throw new OneJsError('Tag not found', 404, '...')
    }
    return tag
  }
}
```

### ❌ INCORRECT - Dead Code

```typescript
// ❌ Unused import
import { Something, AnotherThing } from './somewhere'
import { OnlyThisIsUsed } from './elsewhere'

// ❌ Unused function
function unusedHelper() {
  return 'never called'
}

// ❌ Unused variable
const UNUSED_CONSTANT = 'value'

export class UseCase {
  async execute(input: { id: string }): Promise<Tag> {
    // Only this is used
    return await this.repository.findById(input.id)
  }
}
```

## Completeness Verification

Before finishing any task, verify:

1. ✅ No TODO/FIXME/XXX/HACK comments
2. ✅ No `throw new Error('... not yet implemented')` or similar
3. ✅ All described functionality is implemented
4. ✅ No empty files or files with only comments
5. ✅ Dead code has been removed
6. ✅ All imports are used
7. ✅ All exported functions are used or have documented purpose
8. ✅ **Tests exist for all implemented code** (TDD requirement)
9. ✅ **Test cases list created in REASON phase** (TDD requirement)
10. ✅ **Tests written BEFORE implementation** (RED phase completed)
11. ✅ **All tests pass** (GREEN state achieved)
12. ✅ **Code refactored with tests green** (REFACTOR phase completed)
13. ✅ **Test cases list shows completion status** (RE-EVALUATE phase)
14. ✅ Tests for removed functionality have been deleted (see `.cursor/rules/tdd-cycle.mdc`)
15. ✅ All tests pass (TDD cycle enforces implementation completeness)

**Without following TDD, code cannot be considered complete regardless of implementation quality.**

## Temporary Exceptions (Strict Record)

Code can only be left temporarily incomplete if:

1. There is a clearly documented technical reason
2. It is marked as STUB/TEMPORARY with review date
3. There is a documented plan to complete it
4. It is explicitly requested by the user

### Format for Temporary Exceptions

```typescript
// STUB: Minimal implementation - requires integration with external service X
// Blocker: Service not yet available (date: 2025-01-XX)
// Plan: Complete when service is available (ticket #123)
// Review: 2025-02-XX
async syncWithExternalService(data: Data): Promise<void> {
  // Minimal functional implementation that doesn't block the rest
  this.logger.warn('[MATO:SYNC:EXTERNAL]', 'External service sync pending')
  // ... minimal implementation that allows code to function
}
```

## Integration with Validation

The project includes a validation script (`bun validate:completeness`) that detects:
- TODOs in code
- "Not yet implemented" errors
- Empty files
- Basic dead code

Run this script before considering a task completed.

## Rules Summary

### ✅ DO

- Complete all functionality before finishing
- Remove all TODOs before delivering
- Fully implement all functions
- Clean up dead code and unused items
- Verify everything works before finishing

### ❌ DON'T DO

- Don't leave pending TODOs
- Don't use `throw new Error('not yet implemented')`
- Don't create empty files
- Don't leave partial functionality
- Don't leave dead code uncleaned
- Don't deliver incomplete code

